<TITLE> Police recover youth's body from roof </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 5 (bdnews24.com)--The police have recovered a body from a commercial building's roof in Chittagong city on Wednesday. The dead is Md Jashim, 35, son of Ali Ahmed of Satkania upazila. Jashim used to run a video store jointly. The body was recovered from Royal Plaza's roof at Amtala area adjacent to Reazuddin Bazar at around 10.30am. Mahiuddin Mahmud, OC of Chittagong Sadr Police Station told bdnews24.com that they had suspected that he went to the roof at dawn to have a shower. Mahmud said that he might have slipped on a slab and died. "We are investigating if anyone had pushed him and killed him," the police officer said. The body was handed over his family members after post mortem. No case was filed in this regard till Wednesday afternoon. 
